Version 1.2.0

- Implemented a new search filter for the logger, with optional highlighting and removal of non-matching entries.
- The highlight color can be customized in the MCM settings, and can also be disabled entirely.
- Each log level's color can now be customized in the MCM settings.
- Fixed a crash that occurred when MCM was not installed

Known Issues:

- I haven't been able to fully profile the logger performance with the new search filter, but it may cause some slowdown when filtering a large number of log entries.

Version 1.1.1

- Fixed an issue where the logger would not function while the game was paused.
- Added categories and order to the MCM settings. It looks a lot nicer now!

Known Issues:

- The color coding is still a WIP.

Version 1.1.0

- Added MCM integration for easier settings management.
- Improved color coding in the logger.
- Logger position is retained when toggling the UI off and back on.
- Improved logging performance.
- Replaced the scene heirarchy with a more efficient structure. This should allow for better control over the UI, therefore makes expanding the UI with new features easier in the future.
- Removed "attach" and "detach" functions from the DbgUtils main class, as they were not necessary and ultimately just added extra complexity for no real benefit.
- Handles scene transitions smoother, with persistent UI across scenes.

Known Issues:

- The logger does not function while the game is paused. This is a deeper issue than I expected, and will take a little longer to get figured out.
- The color coding is still a WIP, and may not be fully consistent across all log levels. I will continue to refine this in future updates.

Version 1.0.0:

- Initial release of the project.

Known Issues:

- The logger does not function while the game is paused.
